Fix codex_smoke flake under parallel load

Two fixes:

1. Increase codex app-server health check timeout from 5s to 30s.
   Under parallel test load, the app-server needs more time to start.
   The 5s timeout caused ensure_app_server_running to fail, which sent
   a WebSocket Close frame back through the proxy chain, and the host
   codex CLI reported "failed to connect to remote app server".

2. Include install_codex in the prepared image tag hash.
   Without this, a prepared image built without codex could be reused
   by a pod that needs it (or vice versa) if all other tag inputs match.
